pgTitle: List of countries with McDonald's restaurants

rows.text: First outlet in Creteil in 1972 even though McDonald's officially recognizes the first outlet in Strasbourg in 1979
First drive-thru in Europe opened in Ashgrove, Dublin
Open only to base personnel. Ordinary Cubans cannot access.
(source: Local website 74 in East, North and Central. 40 in West and South)
As of April 2012, Fiji is the only country in the world to still use the 2003 "i'm lovin' it" packaging, even though the other countries are using the 2008 packaging for meals and items.

The company claimed this as McDonald's "100th country" although this calculation included many non-sovereign territories even though McDonald's shut down in Iceland in 2009 it is the 99th country as of November 1, 2009.
McDonald's outlets ceased operation during the Nicaraguan civil war and re-established a presence in 1998 after an absence of two decades.
After some 10 years of trying to enter the Bosnian market with no success, McDonald's opened its first restaurant in BiH on 20 July 2011
Re-opened at The Falls At West Mall in 2011 and has expanded to 5 other locations. McDonald's previously had stores in Trinidad (May 6, 1997 - October 25, 2003) but closed due to low sales.
